==English==

===Noun===
'''[[profit]] [[margin]]'''

# The ratio of [[Net Income]] to [[Net Sales]] of a [[company]] expressed as a [[percentage]].
For example, if a company has $10,000 Net Income and $100,000 Net Sales, then Profit Margin 
equals ($10,000 : $100,000) .10, or 10%.

